observationText: The SK-MEL-23 cell line was derived from a metastatic site of a malignant melanoma.
SK-MEL-23 cells exhibited high levels of BRAF V600E mutation and PTEN loss.
SK-MEL-23 cells were sensitive to the BRAF inhibitor vemurafenib in vitro and in vivo.
SK-MEL-23 cells exhibited increased expression of the melanoma stem cell markers CD271 and JARID1B compared to more differentiated melanoma cell lines.
SK-MEL-23 cells exhibited increased expression of the transcription factor MITF compared to more differentiated melanoma cell lines.
SK-MEL-23 cells were more resistant to the BRAF inhibitor dabrafenib compared to vemurafenib.
SK-MEL-23 cells exhibited increased expression of the anti-apoptotic protein BCL-2 compared to more differentiated melanoma cell lines.
SK-MEL-23 cells exhibited increased expression of the transcription factor SOX10 compared to more differentiated melanoma cell lines.
SK-MEL-23 cells were more sensitive to the combination of the BRAF inhibitor dabrafenib and the MEK inhibitor trametinib compared to either drug alone.
SK-MEL-23 cells exhibited increased expression of the stem cell marker CD20 compared to more differentiated melanoma cell lines.
SK-MEL-23 cells exhibited increased expression of the ABC transporter ABCB5 compared to more differentiated melanoma cell lines, which may contribute to chemoresistance.
SK-MEL-23 cells were resistant to the BRAF inhibitor PLX4720 in vitro.
